originalText.text:
Owner is very helpful. Come here to print, photo copy and scan documents for the Chinese embassy for your visa needs.
If you have to print from phone or laptop, you connect to their WiFi, and choose their printer named Brother. Their WiFi is called netgear. It is $1 per page - front and back printing so $1 for both. I had an easier time printing from phone than from laptop.

LIKE review if it’s helpful. Cheers.

originalText.text: Like others have mentioned, they will attempt to scam you by charging more in "taxes" and by default will not provide you with a receipt. I purchased a phone charger from here for 13.99, which is expensive but, whatever, you pay for convenience. How, then, was my credit card charged 15.79 (12.9% in taxes) when the city/state tax is 8.875%?

originalText.text:
I would like to share my experience regarding what has been the most deceitful convenience store encounter in my life.

While on my way home, I stopped at this convenience store to purchase 6 packs of beer priced at $10.99. However, upon checking my receipt later, I was shocked to discover that I had been charged $18.05 instead. It was only after reaching home that I realized this error, as the cashier had swiftly pressed the "no receipt" button and bid me farewell almost instantaneously.

The discrepancy between the advertised price of $10.99 and the actual charge of $18.05 at this convenience store is truly baffling. The lack of transparency displayed is not only disappointing but also unethical.

This experience has left me feeling deeply dissatisfied and appalled by the dishonest practices of this convenience store. Establishments that engage in such dishonesty should not be allowed to operate without consequence. I sincerely hope that potential customers come across this review and take it into consideration before deciding to make a purchase.
